President Trump welcomed the Houston Astros, the 2017 World Series Champions, to the White House. He praised their victory and their resilience in the face of Hurricane Harvey. The President also thanked the team for their efforts in helping those affected by the hurricane and for their community involvement. He commended individual players for their performances and wished the team success in the upcoming season. The owner and manager of the Astros also expressed their gratitude and pride in the team's accomplishments.